The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 23: Nandan Nilekani has started building a team of infotech experts and government officials to help provide identity numbers to over one billion citizens. He formally took charge as chairman of the Unique Identification Authority of India today. The government, which has earmarked Rs 120 crore for the project, expects to start issuing the unique numbers in the next 12-18 months.                             
	 Calcutta, July 23: The Company Law Board has prevented Harsh Lodha from chairing the upcoming Birla Corporation AGM scheduled for July 27. S. Balasubramanian, the presiding officer of CLBs principal bench, has directed that in case a vote was taken on any item on the agenda during the AGM, the results should not be announced.                            
	 Mumbai, July 23: Sony Corporation today appointed Keki Dadiseth as chairman of Sony India board and senior adviser to the Sony Group with immediate effect. Dadiseth will give strategic advice and support to the Sony Group in India as senior adviser.                             
	 Stuttgart, July 23: Porsche conceded defeat in a power struggle with Volkswagen by axing its CEO, Wendelin Wiedeking, paving the way for VW to merge with the German car maker.                                                                                                                           
